    "content": "<p>A continuous time periodic signal $x(t)$ is</p>\n<p>$$ x(t)=1+2 \\cos 2 \\pi t+2 \\cos 4 \\pi t+2 \\cos 6 \\pi t $$</p>\n<p>If $T$ is the period of $x(t)$, then $\\frac{1}{T} \\int_0^T|x(t)|^2 d t=$________(round off to the nearest integer).</p>",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "7",
    "explanation": "<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &\\text {  }\\\\ &\\begin{aligned} \\frac{1}{T} \\int_0^T|x(t)|^2 d t & =\\text { Power of } x(t) \\\\ & =1+\\frac{2^2}{2}+\\frac{2^2}{2}+\\frac{2^2}{2} \\\\ & =1+2+2+2=7 \\end{aligned} \\end{aligned} $$</p>",
    "topic": null,
