    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The Fourier transform $$X(\\omega)$$ of the signal $$x(t)$$ is given by</p>\n<p>$$X(\\omega ) = 1$$, for $$|\\omega | < {W_0}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 0$$, for $$|\\omega | > {W_0}$$</p>\n<p>Which one of the following statements is true?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$$x(t)$$ tends to be an impulse as $${W_0} \\to \\infty $$."
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$$x(0)$$ decreases as $${W_0}$$ increases."
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "At $$t = {\\pi  \\over {2{W_0}}},x(t) =  - {1 \\over \\pi }$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "At $$t = {\\pi  \\over {2{W_0}}},x(t) = {1 \\over \\pi }$$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p><b>Given :</b> $X(\\omega)= \\begin{cases}1, &amp; \\text { for }|\\omega|&lt;\\omega_0 \\\\ 0, &amp; \\text { for }|\\omega|&gt;\\omega_0\\end{cases}$</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyy4mfwt/2a83e09b-376d-4c55-ab84-5d99eac0d6d8/b3879bd0-48c9-11ef-9c03-5b7518daaafa/file-jaoe38c1lyy4mfwu.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyy4mfwt/2a83e09b-376d-4c55-ab84-5d99eac0d6d8/b3879bd0-48c9-11ef-9c03-5b7518daaafa/file-jaoe38c1lyy4mfwu.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2023 Signals and Systems - Continuous Time Periodic Signal Fourier Series Question 2 English Explanation\">\n\n<p>By taking inverse Fourier transform,</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; x(t)=\\frac{\\sin \\omega_0 t}{\\pi t} \\\\\\\\ &amp; x\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{2 \\omega_0}\\right)=\\frac{2 \\omega_0}{\\pi \\times \\pi} \\sin \\omega_0 \\times \\frac{\\pi}{2 \\omega_0}=\\frac{2 \\omega_0}{\\pi^2} \\sin \\frac{\\pi}{2}=\\frac{2 \\omega_0}{\\pi^2} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>So, option (C) and (D) are wrong.</p>\n\n<p>$$ x(0)=\\underset{t \\rightarrow 0}{\\operatorname{Lt}} \\frac{\\sin \\omega_0 t}{\\pi t}=\\underset{t \\rightarrow 0}{L t} \\frac{\\omega_0 \\cos \\omega_0 t}{\\pi}=\\frac{\\omega_0}{\\pi} $$</p>\n\n<p>So, $x(0) \\propto \\omega_0 \\Rightarrow$ Option (B) is wrong.</p>\n\n<p>When $\\omega_0 \\rightarrow \\infty, X(\\omega)$ will be a D.C signal and inverse Fourier transform of a D.C signal will be impulse signal.</p>\n\n<p>So, option (A) is correct.</p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (A).</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "gate-ee-2023",
    "difficulty": null
