    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The discrete time Fourier series representation of a signal x[n] with period N is written as $$x[n] = \\sum\\nolimits_{k = 0}^{N - 1} {{a_k}{e^{j(2kn\\pi /N)}}} $$. A discrete time periodic signal with period N = 3, has the non-zero Fourier series coefficients : a<sub>$$-$$3</sub> = 2 and a<sub>4</sub> = 1. The signal is</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$$2 + 2{e^{ - \\left( {j{{2\\pi } \\over 6}n} \\right)}}\\cos \\left( {{{2\\pi } \\over 6}n} \\right)$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$$1 + 2{e^{\\left( {j{{2\\pi } \\over 6}n} \\right)}}\\cos \\left( {{{2\\pi } \\over 6}n} \\right)$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$$1 + 2{e^{\\left( {j{{2\\pi } \\over 3}n} \\right)}}\\cos \\left( {{{2\\pi } \\over 6}n} \\right)$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$$2 + 2{e^{\\left( {j{{2\\pi } \\over 6}n} \\right)}}\\cos \\left( {{{2\\pi } \\over 6}n} \\right)$$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given that: $$x[n] = \\sum\\limits_{K = 0}^{N - 1} {{a_K}{e^{j\\left( {{{2\\pi } \\over N}Kn} \\right)}}} $$</p>\n<p>N = 3</p>\n<p>a<sub>$$-$$3</sub> = 2</p>\n<p>a<sub>K</sub> = a<sub>K + N</sub></p>\n<p>a<sub>$$-$$3</sub> = a<sub>$$-$$3 + N</sub> = a<sub>$$-$$3 + 3</sub> = a<sub>0</sub></p>\n<p>a<sub>$$-$$3</sub> = a<sub>0</sub></p>\n<p>a<sub>4</sub> = 1</p>\n<p>a<sub>4</sub> = a$$_{ - 4}^*$$</p>\n<p>a<sub>$$-$$4</sub> = 1</p>\n<p>K = 4</p>\n<p>a<sub>4</sub> = a<sub>4 + 3</sub> = a<sub>7</sub></p>\n<p>a<sub>$$-$$4</sub> = a<sub>$$-$$4 + 3</sub> = a<sub>$$-$$1</sub></p>\n<p>a<sub>$$-$$1</sub> = a<sub>1</sub> = 1</p>\n<p>a<sub>1</sub> = a<sub>4</sub> = 1</p>\n<p>$$x[n] = \\sum\\limits_{K = 0}^{3 - 1} {{a_k}{e^{j\\left( {{{2\\pi } \\over 3}kn} \\right)}}} $$</p>\n<p>$$ = \\sum\\limits_{K = 0}^2 {{a_k}{e^{j\\left( {{{2\\pi } \\over 3}kn} \\right)}}} $$</p>\n<p>$$ = {a_0} + {a_1}{e^{j\\left( {{{2\\pi } \\over 3}n} \\right)}} + {a_2}{e^{j\\left( {{{2\\pi } \\over 3}2n} \\right)}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 2 + 1\\,.\\,{e^{j\\left( {{{2\\pi } \\over 3}n} \\right)}} + 0$$</p>\n<p>$$x[n] = 2 + {e^{j\\left( {{{2\\pi } \\over 3}n} \\right)}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 1 + {e^{j\\left( {{{2\\pi } \\over 3}n} \\right)}} + 1$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 1 + {e^{{{j2\\pi } \\over 3}n}} + {e^{ - {{j2\\pi } \\over 6}n}}\\,.\\,{e^{{{j2\\pi } \\over 6}n}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 1 + {e^{{{j2\\pi } \\over 6}n}}\\left[ {{e^{{{j2\\pi } \\over 6}n}} + {e^{{{j2\\pi } \\over 6}n}}} \\right]$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 1 + 2{e^{{{j2\\pi } \\over 6}n}}\\left[ {{{{e^{{{j2\\pi } \\over 6}n}} + {e^{ - {{j2\\pi } \\over 6}n}}} \\over 2}} \\right]$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 1 + 2{e^{{{j2\\pi } \\over 6}n}}\\cos \\left( {{{2\\pi } \\over 6}n} \\right)$$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "gate-ee-2022",
    "difficulty": null
  },
